&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking for an exciting role in a busy customer service team?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our caseworkers handle a large amount of cases. In this role you will be responsible for supporting all elements of casework and developing the service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;What is critical is your ability to use IT, particularly MS Excel, to keep accurate records and work as part of a busy team. As well as working closely with caseworkers you will also provide valuable support to a wide range of roles, including analysts and senior managers. This will provide an excellent platform for learning, development and future progression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our casework support team are also responsible for communicating with our customers so a can-do, positive and customer focused attitude is a must.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you think you have these skills and would relish the opportunity to learn, develop and progress we are looking forward to hearing from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The application form is your opportunity to tell us about your ability to work as part of a team, provide excellent customer (internal and external) service and be confident using IT. This could be in your current job but could equally be from your other interests and experiences.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whilst we are offering a full time position, applications from part-timers and job-sharers will be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Kallie Taylor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Casework Team Lead - Provider Assurance (Dental Services)&lt;/p&gt;
